did.abstract: The Office of Graduate Student Enrollment Management falls under the Office of Graduate Studies and Academic Affairs. This collection contains reports, programs, registration forms, budgets, minutes, evaluations, publications, attendance statistics, videos, and banners related to the Graduate and Professional School Fair. Materials date from 1978 to 2009, with the bulk of the material falling between 1990 and 2007.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Please cite unpublished materials in the following way:
Please provide the title and date of item, catalog number (if applicable it will be found written on the folder), name of the collection, name of the repository, and location of the repository.

Example: James Oglethorpe to the Trustees, 13 January 1876, RG0001 Series 1, Box 4, Folder 3. Records of the Board of Trustees, Special Collections Research Center, Gelman Library, The George Washington University, Washington, D.C.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Transferred by the Office of Graduate Student Enrollment Management, 08/06/2009 (2009.045).

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into 1 series: Graduate and Professional School Fair

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records of the Graduate Student Enrollment Office contain reports, programs, registration forms, budgets, minutes, evaluations, publications, attendance statistics, videos, and banners all related to the Graduate and Professional School Fair. Materials date from 1978 to 2009, with the bulk of the material falling between 1990 and 2007.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Office of Graduate Student Enrollment Management falls under the Office of Graduate and Special Enrollment Management, the Office of Graduate Studies and Academic Affairs, and finally the Executive Vice President for Academic Affairs.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains material pertaining to the planning and implementation of the Graduate and Professional School Fair. Types of material include programs, reports, registration forms, budges, evaluations, minutes, publications ("Roll Call" Graduate and Law Schools Guide"), attendance statistics, videotapes, and banners.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged by topic, then chronologically. Materials are in the order in which they were sent to the University Archives by the Graduate Student Enrollment Management office.
